org.vadere.state.scenario

Class Topography

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.vadere.state.scenario.Topography

  • public class Topography
extends java.lang.Object
    This class holds the topography of the simulation map. This means it carries the attributes, obstacles, sources, targets and the dynamicelements elements

    • Constructor Summary

      • addBoundary

        public void addBoundary(Obstacle obstacle)
        Adds a given obstacle to the list of obstacles as well as the list of boundary obstacles. This way, the boundary can both be treated like normal obstacles, but can also be removed for writing the topography to file.

      • removeBoundary

        public void removeBoundary()
        Removes the boundaries of a topography

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Call this method to reset the topography to the state before a simulation take place. After this call all generated boundaries, pedestrians (from source) and all listeners will be removed.
